# UI Design Standards

## CSS Variables — Always Use Tokens

Never hardcode colors, shadows, or borders. Use the CSS custom properties defined in `App.css`:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
background: var(--bg-primary);
color: var(--text-secondary);
border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);

/* ❌ BAD */
background: #ffffff;
color: #666;
border: 1px solid #ddd;
```

### Available token groups

| Group | Variables |
|-------|-----------|
| Backgrounds | `--bg-primary`, `--bg-secondary`, `--bg-tertiary` |
| Text | `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-muted` |
| Accent | `--accent-color`, `--accent-hover` |
| Borders | `--border-color`, `--border-color-light` |
| Shadows | `--shadow-sm`, `--shadow-md` |
| Status | `--success-color`, `--error-color` |

## Dark Mode

Dark mode is handled automatically by `[data-theme="dark"]` in `App.css`. Do not add manual dark-mode overrides via inline styles or JavaScript theme checks:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
const isDark = document.body.dataset.theme === 'dark';
style={{ color: isDark ? '#fff' : '#000' }}

// ✅ GOOD — use a CSS variable and let the theme do the work
style={{ color: 'var(--text-primary)' }}
```

## Co-located Stylesheets

Every component gets its own `.css` file with the same name, in the same folder:

```
src/client/components/
  WorkItemCard.tsx
  WorkItemCard.css   ← import './WorkItemCard.css' at the top of the component
```

## Inline Styles

Reserve inline styles for values that are truly dynamic (driven by runtime state). Use CSS classes for everything else:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — dynamic value from state
style={{ opacity: isDragging ? 0.5 : 1, width: `${panelWidth}px` }}

// ❌ BAD — static values belong in CSS
style={{ padding: '8px 12px', borderRadius: '4px' }}
```

## Transitions

Use consistent timing:

- **Micro-interactions** (hover, focus, button states): `transition: all 0.2s ease`
- **Panel / modal animations** (open/close, slide): `transition: all 0.3s ease`

## Typography

Do not override the system font stack. The project uses:

```css
font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, sans-serif;
```

## Spacing & Sizing

Align spacing with existing components — avoid arbitrary magic numbers. Prefer values from the existing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32 px).
